f(x)=\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}
\lim_{x\to-\infty} f(x)
f(x)=\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}
=\frac{2+\frac1x}{(2-\frac1x)^2}
\frac1x
0
=\frac{2+0}{(2-0)^2}
=\frac24
 \lim_{x\to-\infty} f(x)\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}=\frac12
\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}=\frac{\frac2x}{\left(2-\frac1x\right)^2}\text{ and not}\frac{2+\frac1x}{\left(2-\frac1x\right)^2}
\frac1x=h
x\to-\infty, h\to0^-
\lim_{x\to-\infty}\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}=\lim_{h\to0^-}\frac{2h}{(2-h)^2}
0
\frac{2x}{(2x-1)^2}=\frac{2x}{x^2(2-\frac{1}{x})^2}
